Mission.Comments:
Through The Inferno (PvE Caucasus v2.0.4) by deadlyfishes and the 107th JAS
A highly dynamic PvE experience for all modern aircraft.
***SERVER INFO*** Website: throughtheinferno.com Rules: throughtheinferno.com/rules Discord: https://discord.gg/BRF2pcN
***SRS Radio IPs*** SoCal Server 1: socal1.throughtheinferno.com SoCal Server 2: socal2.throughtheinferno.com SoCal Server 3: socal3.throughtheinferno.com SoCal Server 4: socal4.throughtheinferno.com NorCal Server 1: norcal.throughtheinferno.com
(The intro message that pops up when you join an aircraft will let you know which server you are on.)
***USEFUL MISSION TIPS!*** Mission Tasking Tutorial Video (You can copy/paste link from within this breifing) https://youtu.be/xXV2kB_g2oc
Looking for active ground mission locations? You can access the INTEL reports via the Mision Intel Menu in your F10 - Other Menu which is usually bound to your \ key. LL DMS, LL DMM and MGRS formats are available.
Aircraft labled with (CVN-7X) use the Super Carrier Module, (CVN-74) use the free carrier module.
Type "-time" in all chat to get a message that will display the approximate time remaining until the next server restart
Wanna play offline? We offer the same "Through The Inferno" experience in a single player package as well! Check the missions out here: throughtheinferno.com/singleplayermissions
***SERVER RULES*** The server is monitored by admins and moderators who enforce our server rules. Find our in-game and community rules here: throughtheinferno.com/rules
***We use SRS Radio*** Using Simple Radio Standalone is highly encouraged on this server. You can find download links on our website. We often have active ATC and AWACs.
(The intro message that pops up when you join an aircraft will let you know which server you are on.)

WTTI - "The Inferno" Music Radio Station: Non-stop adrenaline pumping music tracks over SRS 123.0 MHz
***BULLSEYE = WPT 29 || SOCHI***
SMOKE COLORS? WHAT DO THEY MEAN HERE? Friendly: White - CTLD Crate and Troop Zone for HELOS Blue - Wounded Pilot, HELOS and PROP PLANES can rescue these guys.
Enemy: Red - Single ground unit target being lased and marked by JTAC. Check JTAC Status in F10 Other for more details.
